{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2f156acc-5bb6-4977-884f-3f16c4823457","content":"No workflow files found in this directory. Here's a general guide for switching to NuGet trusted publishing with OIDC:\n\n### 1. Configure NuGet.org\nOn [nuget.org](https://www.nuget.org), go to your package → **Manage** → **Trusted Publishers** and add a GitHub Actions publisher with your repo, branch, and optionally the workflow/environment name.\n\n### 2. Update your workflow\n\n**Before (API key):**\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**After (OIDC):**\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n        with:\n          dotnet-version: '8.x'\n      - run: dotnet build -c Release\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n      - run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Key changes:\n1. **Add `permissions.id-token: write`** — enables the OIDC token request\n2. **Remove `--api-key`** — the `dotnet` CLI automatically uses the OIDC token when no key is provided and `id-token` permission is granted\n3. **Delete the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret** from your repo settings once verified\n4. **Use `setup-dotnet@v4`** or later (it handles the OIDC handshake with NuGet)\n\n### Optional: Use an environment for extra protection\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    environment: nuget-publish   # matches what you set on nuget.org\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write\n      contents: read\n```\n\nThis removes long-lived secrets entirely — the trust is based on your repo identity via GitHub's OIDC provider.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cf6d192a-a677-466e-93d6-a42431d204c1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No workflow files found in the repository. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to trusted publishing (OIDC). Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":582,"requestId":"5C57:283B0A:F4431A:133B13E:69FFD82D"},"id":"5adb9184-a788-49cb-81ec-19d3b8816163","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:58:33.633Z","parentId":"3cdff535-42c9-4aff-afaf-fa051b575add"}
